(6, 'doc-002', 0, 'Leave Policy: Employees are entitled to 24 days of paid leave per year (2 days per month). Leave quota is credited on the 1st of every month. Unused leave can be carried forward up to a maximum of 30 days. Leave encashment is allowed at year-end for a maximum of 15 days.', 1, '0.1,0.3,0.5,0.7,0.9'),
(7, 'doc-002', 1, 'Types of Leave: Casual Leave (CL), Sick Leave (SL), Privilege Leave (PL), Maternity Leave (90 days for women), Paternity Leave (7 days for men), Bereavement Leave (5 days for immediate family). Casual and Sick leaves are interchangeable and part of the 24-day annual quota.', 2, '0.2,0.4,0.6,0.8,0.1'),
(8, 'doc-002', 2, 'Leave Application Process: Leave must be applied through the HR portal at least 3 days in advance for planned leave. Emergency leave can be applied within 24 hours with manager approval. Leave requests require manager approval. Multiple days leave (>5 days) requires department head approval.', 2, '0.3,0.5,0.7,0.9,0.2'),
(9, 'doc-002', 3, 'Leave During Notice Period: Employees serving notice period can only take leave with special approval. Unutilized leave during notice period will not be encashed. Medical emergencies are exempted with proper documentation. Maximum 5 days leave allowed during 30-day notice period.', 3, '0.4,0.6,0.8,0.1,0.3');

